<plot>Gazing is the most fundamental of all cognitive activities. From the first time we recognize "self" in the mirror, as an infant, we obtain consciousness. It allows the senses, and us to acquire knowledge and understanding through thought, experience which results in perception, sensation, notion and intuition. Jane Milton awakens to an environment where the relationships between the observer and the observed analyze beauty to the point of annihilation. Men look at women, women look at women, women look at themselves and so does the audience: we are all guilty. Is empowerment obtained simply by the response of taking control?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?643030</url></doc>
